Prevent GLES1 alpha-test state from calling unavailable host entry points.

gfxstream's fixed-function translator already treats GL_ALPHA_TEST as emulated
state when its backing context is OpenGL core profile or GLES. glAlphaFunc and
glAlphaFuncx missed that split and unconditionally called the host dispatcher.
On GLES-backed hosts that dispatcher entry is null, so a legacy game issuing
glAlphaFunc can segfault the entire crosvm process.

Keep alpha-function updates on the compatibility-profile path and avoid the
unavailable host function on the two shader-emulated paths.

diff --git a/host/gl/glestranslator/gles_cm/gles_cm_imp.cpp b/host/gl/glestranslator/gles_cm/gles_cm_imp.cpp
--- a/host/gl/glestranslator/gles_cm/gles_cm_imp.cpp
+++ b/host/gl/glestranslator/gles_cm/gles_cm_imp.cpp
@@ -443,6 +443,11 @@ GL_API void GL_APIENTRY  glAlphaFunc( GLenum func, GLclampf ref) {
     GET_CTX()
     GLES_CM_TRACE()
     SET_ERROR_IF(!GLEScmValidate::alphaFunc(func),GL_INVALID_ENUM);
+    // Alpha testing is fixed-function state that is unavailable on both core
+    // profile OpenGL and GLES hosts. CoreProfileEngine already treats
+    // GL_ALPHA_TEST enable/disable as emulated state, so do not dispatch the
+    // corresponding host-only entry point on those paths.
+    if (isCoreProfile() || isGles2Gles()) return;
     ctx->dispatcher().glAlphaFunc(func,ref);
 }
 
@@ -451,6 +456,7 @@ GL_API void GL_APIENTRY  glAlphaFuncx( GLenum func, GLclampx ref) {
     GET_CTX()
     GLES_CM_TRACE()
     SET_ERROR_IF(!GLEScmValidate::alphaFunc(func),GL_INVALID_ENUM);
+    if (isCoreProfile() || isGles2Gles()) return;
     ctx->dispatcher().glAlphaFunc(func,X2F(ref));
 }
 
